      "id": "339a9cbe80c2c11f",
      "text": "The general objective of the study to examine the causes of conflicts between Fulani herdsmen and farmers in Saki West Local Government Area and review the age-old relationship to determine the source(s) of the conflict. Furthermore, it is a well-known fact that perception plays a major role in conflict generation and management. What are the perceptual filters that govern the relationship?  Perceptual filters include culture, ethnicity, gender and sexuality, knowledge, previous experiences in managing the conflicts, i.e. issues that may condition the attitudes of the parties to the present conflict (Tung –Tooney 1994). For instance, how much respect does an average Yoruba have for a Bororo Fulani and vice-versa?"
    },
    {
      "type": "markdown",
      "id": "4fbd70d04b93172f",
      "text": "Furthermore, what are the roles of the law enforcement agencies in mediating the conflicts? Are they above board? Do they have the resources and expertise to manage the conflict? What about the issue of climate change? Are there genuine and concerted efforts to address the problems of desertification, deforestation, pollution and the resultant depletion of the ozone layer which are some of the causes of climate change?"
    },
    {
      "type": "markdown",
      "id": "b7d8d7d6f11475ec",
      "text": "The study will also examine the symbiotic, economic and social relationship between the Farmers and the Fulani herders and consider the efficacy of previous conflict management efforts in the light of today’s challenges and realities."
