      "type": "markdown",
      "id": "2bdeb4a6f6cbd848",
      "text": "(5) To suggest ways and means of achieving a lasting solution to the recurring conflicts between Fulani Herdsmen and Farmers in Saki West  Local Government Area."
    },
    {
      "type": "markdown",
      "id": "bb8b90a9a27b3cfe",
      "text": "This study highlights the cultural, economic, social and ethnic differences that could be conflict triggers between Pastoralists and Farmers in Saki West Local Government Area of Oyo State. It also brings into focus, the traditional conflict prevention mechanisms which facilitated the peaceful cohabitation of Fulanis and Farmers in the area and the factors that led to the breakdown of these time tested measures which has now resulted in the periodic eruption of violence between the two groups. The study also reviews the role(s) of government agencies responsible of the resolution of the conflicts and examines how effective these have been."
    },
    {
      "type": "markdown",
      "id": "b290afbe299edddb",
      "text": "The key role of the State Government in formulating and implementing agricultural policies and programs that impact on the herdsmen and farmers relationship is also examined to see how effective the policies have been."
    },
    {
      "type": "markdown",
      "id": "0f1164d3a6cdb14e",
      "text": "The study further offers suggestions on ways of establishing alternative mechanisms that would ensure restoration of the erstwhile relative peaceful communal relationship between the two groups. It also investigates the effect of failure of efforts at transforming if not preventing incessant conflicts between Fulani Herdsmen (i.e. Pastoralists) and farmers in the area. In other words, the study interrogates the nexus between the incidence of conflict and economic malaise occasioned by bad governance. "
